    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G7 (serial; depends on 024 + 025 + 026; blocks 030)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>024 (InsightsQueryToolHandler tool wiring), 025 (subject resolution + HTTP client), 026 (two-path InsightsResponseRenderer)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, error-handling, insights, retry</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire complete, contract-binding error handling into the `InsightsResponseRenderer`
    component shipped by task 026. The Insights Engine R2 binding contract v1.0
    (`notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md` §5.1) defines a stable
    12-code error matrix. R5 MUST handle every code with the per-code user-facing
    message in column 4 of that matrix — no raw stack traces, no document content,
    no prompt text, no LLM raw output leaks to the user (per integration brief §5.2
    + ADR-018 + ADR-019).

    Two special-case retry policies (per spec FR-16 + plan.md D2-19):
    - **503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + no `forceMode`**: if R5 has an
      intent signal available client-side (e.g., user invoked via the
      `/ask-insights playbook ...` or `/ask-insights rag ...` slash command per
      task 019), retry ONCE with the explicit `forceMode` set. If no intent signal
      is available (pure natural-language tool-call), do NOT retry — surface the
      generic "temporarily disabled" UX.
    - **500 `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`**: retry ONCE with 1s backoff. On
      second 500, surface the error to the user (no further retries — strict
      no-infinite-loop policy per integration brief §5.1 column 4).

    All other error codes are **non-retryable** by the client:
    - 400-class (5 codes — `query.required`, `subject.required`, `subject.invalid`,
      `forceMode.invalid`, `conversationContext.invalid`): client-side bugs or
      malformed inputs; surfacing the per-code message is the correct response,
      retry would just fail again.
    - 401: re-authenticate via existing `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` refresh; if
      persists, surface "Your session expired".
    - 429: honor `Retry-After` header per ADR-016 — surface "Slow down a moment"
      with timer; do NOT auto-retry inside the renderer.
    - 503 `ai.insights.disabled` / `ai.rag.disabled` /
      `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`: kill-switches / config bugs;
      surfacing the per-code message is correct.

    `x-correlation-id` propagation (spec FR-17 / SC-16): the correlation ID
    generated per Assistant turn by the tool handler (task 024 Step 4 generates;
    task 025 HTTP client propagates) MUST be surfaced in the error UI as an
    OPAQUE operator-debugging key — visible (so support can ask "what's your
    request ID?"), but NOT used by the user to reason about the error. The
    correlationId is treated as untrusted display text — render with the same
    escaping discipline as any other untrusted string.

    This task is PURE FRONTEND. ZERO BFF code change. Publish-size delta = 0 MB
    (no `dotnet publish` measurement required, but confirm delta = 0 in task
    notes per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React / TypeScript developer with deep familiarity of the Spaarke AI
    widget framework + Fluent UI v9 + `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` /
    `authenticatedFetch` + ADR-019 ProblemDetails parsing. Understands the
    Insights v1.0 binding contract (integration brief), the
    `InsightsResponseRenderer` two-path renderer (task 026), and the per-turn
    correlation-id propagation chain (task 024 generates → task 025 HTTP client
    propagates → this task surfaces in UI). Familiar with ADR-016 (rate-limit
    honoring), ADR-018 (no information leakage), ADR-019 (ProblemDetails
    extension parsing), ADR-028 (Auth v2 reauth flow), R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5
    (Insights Zone B consumer boundary).
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `InsightsResponseRenderer` (and its co-located error-handling utility
    module — extracted at this task's discretion) handles all 12 error codes from
    integration brief §5.1 with the column-4 user-facing message. Two retry
    policies are implemented:

    1. 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + intent signal available → retry
       once with explicit `forceMode`.
    2. 500 `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR` → retry once with 1s backoff.

    No other error code triggers an auto-retry. `Retry-After` (429) is rendered
    as a countdown / "try again in N seconds" hint — the user clicks "Retry" to
    re-issue the request manually (no auto-retry).

    `correlationId` is surfaced in the error UI as an opaque ops-debugging key
    (visible, copyable, but visually de-emphasized — small mono-font under the
    user-facing message). The full ProblemDetails error envelope (`status`,
    `title`, `detail`, `errorCode`, `correlationId`) is preserved in
    component-internal state for telemetry / Console-log diagnostics but is
    NEVER rendered to the user beyond the column-4 message + correlationId.

    No raw stack traces, no document content, no prompt text, no LLM raw output
    appears in the rendered error UI. Verified by unit test (Test 6) that
    intentionally injects a fabricated error response containing
    document-content-like text and asserts none of it reaches the rendered DOM.

    Unit tests cover all 12 codes + both retry paths + correlation-id surfacing
    + no-leakage assertion + ADR-016 `Retry-After` honoring. Quality gates pass.
    BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB confirmed.
  </goal>

