  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 / §10 / ADR-013 §3.5 Zone B boundary">R5 is a Zone B consumer of the Insights contract. This task consumes the contract's error envelope (ProblemDetails with `errorCode` extension) — does NOT couple to any Insights internals. No `import` from Insights server-side types; the error envelope is parsed via R5-local TypeScript types matching the contract's wire shape.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 / reuse mandate">MUST integrate with the EXISTING `InsightsResponseRenderer` shipped by task 026 — do NOT create a parallel error-rendering component, do NOT create a parallel HTTP retry framework. If error-handling logic needs extraction for testability, extract into a co-located utility module (e.g., `insights-error-handler.ts`) imported by the renderer — NOT into a new package.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16 (12 error codes — binding)">MUST handle ALL 12 contract error codes from integration brief §5.1 with the column-4 user-facing message. The 12 codes are: 400 `query.required`, 400 `subject.required`, 400 `subject.invalid`, 400 `forceMode.invalid`, 400 `conversationContext.invalid`, 401 (no errorCode — auth challenge), 429 (no errorCode — rate-limit default), 503 `ai.insights.disabled`, 503 `ai.rag.disabled`, 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled`, 503 `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`, 500 `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`. Per-code messages from integration brief §5.1 column 4 are the user-facing source of truth.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16 / plan.md D2-19 (special retry — 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled`)">If response is 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` AND `forceMode` was NOT set on the original request AND R5 has an intent signal available client-side (slash command path with explicit mode known), retry ONCE with `forceMode` set to the inferred mode. If `forceMode` was already set on the original request, do NOT retry — the classifier is irrelevant when `forceMode` is set, so receiving this code with `forceMode` set indicates a contract bug or BFF misclassification (surface the error). If no intent signal is available client-side (pure natural-language path), do NOT retry — surface generic "temporarily disabled" UX.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16 / plan.md D2-19 (special retry — 500)">500 `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR` → retry ONCE with 1s backoff. On second 500, surface the error to the user. NO infinite-loop retries. Retry counter MUST be tracked per-request (not per-component / per-session) so two consecutive user-initiated requests can each get one retry.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17 / SC-16 (correlation-id propagation)">`x-correlation-id` is generated per Assistant turn upstream (task 024). This task SURFACES it in the error UI as an opaque ops-debugging key. The correlationId MUST be visible (copyable for support tickets) but visually de-emphasized — NEVER the primary UX surface. Treated as untrusted display text (the value comes from a server response header; render with the same escaping as any other untrusted string — Fluent `Text` component default escapes; do NOT inject as HTML).</constraint>
    <constraint source="integration brief §5.2 + ADR-018 (no information leakage)">Errors NEVER include document content, prompt text, LLM raw output, or stack traces. The contract enforces this server-side; this task enforces it client-side by rendering ONLY the column-4 message + correlationId + optional `Retry-After` countdown (on 429). Server-supplied `detail` field MAY contain operator-relevant context per ADR-019 — R5 logs it to Console for diagnostics but does NOT render it to the user.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019 (ProblemDetails parsing)">Error responses are `application/problem+json` per integration brief §5. Parse `status`, `title`, `detail`, `errorCode` (stable extension), `correlationId` (stable extension). Use loose parsing — unknown extensions pass through unchanged for forward-compat (v1.1).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016 (rate-limit honoring)">429 responses carry `Retry-After` header per ADR-016 + `ai-context` policy (60/min/oid aggregate). Renderer parses `Retry-After` (seconds) and shows a countdown / "try again in N seconds" hint. Renderer does NOT auto-retry on 429 — the user clicks "Retry" manually. Aggregate budget includes `/ask` + `/search` + `/assistant/query` per integration brief §11.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 (Auth v2 reauth flow)">401 responses (no `errorCode` — auth challenge) trigger the existing `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` token refresh flow. If token refresh succeeds, single retry. If token refresh fails (e.g., user's session truly expired), surface "Your session expired". MUST use the existing reauth helper — do NOT implement parallel reauth logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code changed). Confirm in task notes; no `dotnet publish` measurement required for this pure-frontend task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 / ADR-018 (no new feature flags)">This task introduces NO new feature flags. The two retry policies are unconditional client-side behavior. Threshold tuning (e.g., 1s backoff value) is hard-coded per integration brief column 4 — does NOT need to be a config knob.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.1 forward-compat">Phase 1.5 contract is forward-compatible. The error envelope MAY gain additional extensions in v1.1 (e.g., `suggestedAction`, `helpUrl`). Renderer MUST preserve unknown extensions in component-internal state (Console-logged for diagnostics) but ignore them in the rendered UI in v1.0. v1.1 enhancements are a follow-up task (out of scope here).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F test obligation">This task is pure frontend (no `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` changes), so the BFF test obligation does not apply. However, the R5 §3.7 frontend-test discipline DOES apply: PRs adding meaningful frontend logic MUST add/update tests in the corresponding `__tests__` directory. This task adds unit tests covering the full 12-code matrix + both retry paths + correlationId surfacing + no-leakage assertion.</constraint>
  </constraints>

