          envelope shape the tool handler / HTTP client surface to the
          renderer (the `InsightsToolException` fields from task 024 Step 4 +
          task 025 Step N — verify alignment).
      (c) Read task 019 POML — confirm the slash command path records the
          `intentSignal` (this task's retry policy depends on that signal
          being available client-side).
      (d) Read ADR-016 (rate-limit + Retry-After), ADR-018 (no information
          leakage — read §"Errors NEVER include" enumeration), ADR-019
          (ProblemDetails wire format), ADR-028 (Auth v2 reauth helper API).
      (e) Read the existing `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` + reauth-flow helper
          source to confirm the API surface for the 401 retry.
      (f) Identify the location of the `InsightsResponseRenderer` shipped by
          task 026 — likely `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/...` or
          `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/...`. Confirm
          exact path from task 026's `<outputs>` section.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author the 12-code matrix + message constants">
      Author the canonical TypeScript const map encoding all 12 codes →
      user-facing messages. Co-locate with the renderer (or in a new
      `insights-error-messages.ts` module imported by the renderer).

      The 12 entries (verbatim from integration brief §5.1 column 4):

      1. `query.required` (HTTP 400) — "I couldn't understand the question."
      2. `subject.required` (HTTP 400) — same as `query.required` (likely
         Assistant wiring bug; same UX).
      3. `subject.invalid` (HTTP 400) — generic "Couldn't identify the
         entity — try again from a matter, project, or invoice context."
      4. `forceMode.invalid` (HTTP 400) — generic Assistant bug; surface
         "Something went wrong — try again." (Assistant team fixes wiring.)
      5. `conversationContext.invalid` (HTTP 400) — surface "Conversation
         context too long — starting a fresh thread." (R5 truncates +
         retries silently in v1.0; this task surfaces the UX of the
         truncation hint.)
      6. 401 (no `errorCode`) — synthesized key `auth.401`: trigger reauth
         flow (Step 5 below); if reauth fails, "Your session expired —
         sign in again."
      7. 429 (no `errorCode`) — synthesized key `rate-limit.429`: "Slow
         down a moment — you can try again in N seconds." (N from
         `Retry-After` header.)
      8. `ai.insights.disabled` (HTTP 503) — "Insights temporarily disabled
         — please try again later."
      9. `ai.rag.disabled` (HTTP 503) — "Knowledge search temporarily
         disabled — please try again later." (If `forceMode: "playbook"`
         was set on original request and BFF returned this code anyway,
         log diagnostic — shouldn't happen per contract.)
     10. `ai.intent-classification.disabled` (HTTP 503) — see Step 4 retry
         policy. If retry not applicable: "Insights temporarily disabled
         — please try again later."
     11. `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured` (HTTP 503) —
         "Something's misconfigured — try again later or contact support."
         (Deployment bug per integration brief; correlationId surfaces for
         ops.)
     12. `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR` (HTTP 500) — see Step 4
         retry policy. After retry exhausted: "Something went wrong —
         try again. If this keeps happening, contact support with this
         ID: &lt;correlationId&gt;."

      Final messages MUST exactly match integration brief §5.1 column 4
      wording where the brief provides verbatim text; where the brief gives
      only behavioral guidance (e.g., "Surface 'I couldn't understand the
      question'") use the quoted text as-is. Cross-reference task notes
      `notes/task-029-error-message-matrix.md` against the brief at PR review
      time.

      Optional UX polish (out of scope for this task; capture in R6 backlog):
      "Try again" affordance below the message for retry-eligible codes;
      "Sign in again" CTA for 401-after-reauth-fail.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author the retry-decision state machine">
      Create `insights-retry-policy.ts` (or co-locate inside the renderer's
      module). Implement `decideRetry(response, originalRequest, attemptNumber)`
      per the knowledge pattern in &lt;knowledge&gt;.

      Pseudo-implementation (binding):

      ```typescript
      export type RetryDecision =
        | { kind: 'no-retry' }
        | { kind: 'retry-with-force-mode'; forceMode: 'playbook' | 'rag' }
        | { kind: 'retry-after-backoff'; backoffMs: number };

      export function decideRetry(
        response: { status: number; errorCode?: string },
        originalRequest: { forceMode?: 'playbook' | 'rag' | null; intentSignal?: 'playbook' | 'rag' | null },
        attemptNumber: number
      ): RetryDecision {
        if (attemptNumber &gt;= 2) return { kind: 'no-retry' };

        // 503 ai.intent-classification.disabled + no forceMode + intent signal known
        if (
          response.status === 503 &amp;&amp;
          response.errorCode === 'ai.intent-classification.disabled' &amp;&amp;
          !originalRequest.forceMode &amp;&amp;
          (originalRequest.intentSignal === 'playbook' || originalRequest.intentSignal === 'rag')
        ) {
          return { kind: 'retry-with-force-mode', forceMode: originalRequest.intentSignal };
        }

        // 500 generic internal error
        if (
          response.status === 500 &amp;&amp;
          response.errorCode === 'INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR'
        ) {
          return { kind: 'retry-after-backoff', backoffMs: 1000 };
        }

        return { kind: 'no-retry' };
      }
      ```

      The state machine is COMPLETE for v1.0 — no other code triggers
      auto-retry. Document in module-level JSDoc + a comment block citing
      integration brief §5.1 + spec FR-16 + plan.md D2-19 as the binding
      contract.

      Wire the state machine into `InsightsResponseRenderer`'s error path:
      on receiving an error envelope, call `decideRetry(...)` → if
      `no-retry`, render the per-code message; if `retry-with-force-mode`,
      re-issue the request via task 025's HTTP client with `forceMode` set
      + correlationId carried forward (same correlationId across retry —
      it's the same logical Assistant turn) + render loading state until
      retry resolves; if `retry-after-backoff`, `await new Promise(r =&gt; setTimeout(r, backoffMs))`
      then re-issue via task 025's HTTP client (same correlationId) +
      render loading state. On the retry's response, run the matrix again
      with `attemptNumber === 2` (guaranteed no further retry per the
      state machine).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire 401 reauth via existing `@spaarke/auth`">
      Identify the existing reauth helper from `@spaarke/auth` (`useAuth()`
      hook or `authenticatedFetch` wrapper — task 025 already uses one of
      these). On 401:
      1. Call the existing reauth helper.
      2. If success → single retry (counts as attemptNumber === 2 in the
         retry-decision state machine; no further retries possible).
      3. If failure → render "Your session expired — sign in again." (column 4 wording, exact).

      MUST use the existing helper; do NOT implement parallel auth refresh
      logic. Cross-reference task 025's HTTP client implementation to
      ensure the reauth chain is unified.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire 429 Retry-After parsing + countdown UX">
      On 429:
      1. Extract `Retry-After` header from the response (parse as RFC 7231
         delta-seconds integer OR HTTP-date — handle both per ADR-016).
      2. Render countdown UX: "Slow down a moment — you can try again in
         &lt;N&gt; seconds." Countdown decrements every second.
      3. When countdown reaches 0, show a "Try again" affordance. User
         clicks manually → re-issue via task 025's HTTP client.
      4. Do NOT auto-retry — user must click. (ADR-016 + binding contract.)

      Aggregate budget note: 60/min/oid across `/ask` + `/search` +
      `/assistant/query` per integration brief §11. The renderer treats
      the 429 the same regardless of which endpoint caused the budget
      exhaustion — server returns `Retry-After`; client honors.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire correlationId surfacing + opaque-display discipline">
      On every error rendering path, surface the `correlationId` extension
      from the ProblemDetails envelope:
      - Render below the user message in small mono-font.
      - Provide a copy-to-clipboard affordance.
      - Treat as untrusted display text (do not inject as HTML; use Fluent
        `Text` component's default escaping).
      - If correlationId is absent (shouldn't happen per contract — log
        diagnostic if it does), omit the section entirely (don't render
        "Unknown ID" or similar; the absence is itself signal).

      Example JSX shape:

      ```tsx
      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;Text&gt;{userFacingMessage}&lt;/Text&gt;
        {correlationId &amp;&amp; (
          &lt;div className={styles.correlationId}&gt;
            &lt;Text size={100} font="monospace"&gt;{correlationId}&lt;/Text&gt;
            &lt;Button appearance="subtle" icon={&lt;Copy24Regular /&gt;} onClick={() =&gt; navigator.clipboard.writeText(correlationId)} aria-label="Copy ID" /&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        )}
      &lt;/div&gt;
      ```

      Use existing copy-to-clipboard utility from `@spaarke/ui-components`
      if one exists (reuse mandate per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1); fall back to
      inline `navigator.clipboard.writeText` otherwise.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Wire no-leakage discipline (ADR-018)">
      The rendered UI MUST contain ONLY:
      - The column-4 user-facing message for the matched error code.
      - The `correlationId` (opaque ops-debugging key).
      - For 429: the `Retry-After` countdown + manual "Try again" CTA.
      - For 401-after-reauth-fail: "Sign in again" CTA.

      The rendered UI MUST NOT contain:
      - `detail` field text (Console-logged for diagnostics; NOT rendered).
      - `title` field text (NOT rendered).
      - Any `[key: string]: unknown` extension values from forward-compat
        index signature (NOT rendered; Console-logged).
      - `status` HTTP code (NOT rendered; redundant with the code-mapped
        message).
      - Anything resembling stack traces, document content, prompt text,
        or LLM raw output.

      Author a "leakage canary" unit test (Test 6 in Step 9):
      - Construct a fabricated error envelope with `detail = "DRAFT —
        Acme APA: This Agreement is between..."`, `title = "Internal
        Server Error"`, and a fabricated `_internalContext = "system
        prompt text..."` extension.
      - Render with this envelope.
      - Assert: rendered DOM does NOT contain "DRAFT — Acme APA", "Internal
        Server Error", or "system prompt text".
      - Assert: rendered DOM DOES contain the column-4 message for the code.
      - Assert: Console-log captured the `detail` + extensions for
        diagnostics.

      This test is the LOAD-BEARING regression guard for ADR-018
      compliance. NEVER skip / disable.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Author unit tests (all 12 codes + retry + correlation + no-leakage)">
      Add a unit test file `insights-response-renderer.error-handling.test.tsx`
      (or extend task 026's renderer test file with a new `describe` block).

      Required test coverage:

      - **Test 1 (12-code matrix — exhaustive)**: For each of the 12 codes,
        assert the rendered DOM contains the correct column-4 user-facing
        message. Use `test.each(...)` table to enumerate the 12 entries —
        prevents accidental skip of a code in future maintenance.
      - **Test 2 (retry — 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + intent
        signal known)**: Mock task 025's HTTP client. First call returns
        503 with errorCode. Second call (retry) returns 200 success. Assert
        the retry was issued with `forceMode: <intentSignal>` set + same
        correlationId carried forward. Assert final rendered DOM shows the
        success result, not the error message.
      - **Test 3 (retry — 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + NO
        intent signal)**: Mock returns 503 with errorCode. Assert NO retry
        is issued (HTTP client called exactly once). Assert rendered DOM
        shows the generic "temporarily disabled" message.
      - **Test 4 (retry — 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` +
        forceMode already on original)**: Mock returns 503 with errorCode.
        Original request had forceMode set. Assert NO retry (edge case —
        contract bug; log diagnostic). Assert rendered DOM shows generic
        message.
      - **Test 5 (retry — 500 INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR with 1s
        backoff)**: Mock first call returns 500. Mock second call (after
        ≥1s) returns 200 success. Use fake timers to assert backoff
        timing. Assert final rendered DOM shows the success result.
      - **Test 6 (retry — 500 on BOTH calls)**: First + second call both
        500. Assert exactly 2 HTTP calls (no third). Assert final
        rendered DOM shows the column-4 message for `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`
        + correlationId.
      - **Test 7 (no-leakage canary)**: Per Step 8 specification — assert
        `detail` / `title` / unknown extensions / fake document content /
        fake stack traces do NOT reach rendered DOM.
      - **Test 8 (correlationId surfacing + escaping)**: Assert
        correlationId renders in DOM, copy-to-clipboard affordance works,
        XSS-attempt correlationId (e.g., `&lt;script&gt;alert(1)&lt;/script&gt;`)
        renders as escaped text (Fluent `Text` default escape), NOT
        injected as HTML.
      - **Test 9 (429 + Retry-After parsing — delta-seconds)**: Mock
        returns 429 with `Retry-After: 30`. Assert countdown UX renders
        "30 seconds". Use fake timers to advance to 0; assert "Try
        again" CTA appears.
      - **Test 10 (429 + Retry-After parsing — HTTP-date)**: Mock returns
        429 with `Retry-After: <future HTTP-date>`. Assert countdown
        computes correct delta. Assert no auto-retry — user clicks CTA
        to retry manually.
      - **Test 11 (401 reauth — success)**: Mock returns 401. Mock
        `@spaarke/auth` reauth helper returns success. Assert single
        retry issued post-reauth. Final rendered DOM = success result.
      - **Test 12 (401 reauth — failure)**: Mock returns 401. Mock reauth
        helper returns failure. Assert rendered DOM shows "Your session
        expired — sign in again." with sign-in CTA.

      Co-locate tests in the test directory adjacent to the renderer
      (matching task 026's `__tests__/` structure).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new files (retry policy module +
      error message map + renderer error-path additions + test file). Run
      `adr-check` skill against the same; verify:

      - **ADR-018 (no information leakage)**: Test 7 (leakage canary) PASSES;
        rendered UI contains ONLY column-4 message + correlationId
        (+ Retry-After UX + reauth CTA where applicable). Confirmed via
        explicit grep of renderer error-path for any reference to `detail`,
        `title`, or unknown extensions in JSX.
      - **ADR-016 (rate-limit honoring)**: Tests 9 + 10 PASS; no auto-retry
        on 429; `Retry-After` parsed correctly (delta-seconds + HTTP-date).
      - **ADR-019 (ProblemDetails parsing)**: TypeScript type with
        forward-compat index signature; all 5 stable fields parsed
        (`status`, `title`, `detail`, `errorCode`, `correlationId`);
        unknown extensions Console-logged but not rendered.
      - **ADR-028 (Auth v2 reauth)**: Test 11 + 12 PASS; uses existing
        `@spaarke/auth` reauth helper; no parallel auth logic. Verified
        by grep of renderer file for any `fetch(...)` or auth-related
        imports outside `@spaarke/auth`.
      - **ADR-013 §3.5 (Zone B boundary)**: No imports from
        `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/...` in the renderer files. Error
        envelope parsed via R5-local TypeScript types matching the
        contract wire shape.
      - **R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (reuse mandate)**: Renderer integrates with
        EXISTING `InsightsResponseRenderer` from task 026; no parallel
        error-rendering component created. Verified by grep + reviewer
        inspection.
      - **R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new feature flags)**: Two retry policies
        are unconditional; backoff timing hard-coded per contract; no
        config knob introduced.

      All gates MUST pass before marking the task complete.

      Confirm BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (pure frontend; no BFF code
      changed). Record in task notes.

      No CVE scan required for this task (no new packages added; uses
      existing `@spaarke/auth`, `@spaarke/ui-components`, Fluent v9).
      Confirm in task notes that no new dependencies were introduced.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`:
      029 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to the next pending task per
      CLAUDE.md §7 (likely 030 — Insights tool smoke tests). Record in
