    <criterion testable="true">All 12 error codes from integration brief §5.1 are handled with the column-4 user-facing message. Confirmed by Test 1 (exhaustive `test.each` matrix — one assertion per code) + cross-reference of `insights-error-messages.ts` against `notes/task-029-error-message-matrix.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + no `forceMode` on original + intent signal available → retry issued ONCE with `forceMode` set to intent signal; same correlationId carried forward. Confirmed by Test 2.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + no intent signal → NO retry; generic "temporarily disabled" UX. Confirmed by Test 3.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` + `forceMode` already on original → NO retry (edge case; log diagnostic); generic UX. Confirmed by Test 4.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">500 `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR` → retry ONCE with 1s backoff; second 500 surfaces error (no further retries). Confirmed by Tests 5 + 6 (success on retry + failure on retry).</criterion>
