    <criterion testable="true">**No information leakage (ADR-018)**: rendered DOM contains ONLY column-4 message + correlationId (+ Retry-After UX + reauth CTA where applicable). `detail`, `title`, unknown extensions, fabricated stack traces, fabricated document content NEVER reach rendered DOM. Confirmed by Test 7 (leakage canary) — load-bearing regression guard.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`correlationId` surfaced in error UI as opaque ops-debugging key — visible (copyable for support tickets), visually de-emphasized (small mono-font), escaped as untrusted display text (Fluent `Text` default escape — XSS-attempt correlationId renders as escaped text, NOT injected as HTML). Confirmed by Test 8.</criterion>
